"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-02-olympics-2024-rosemary-chukwuma-qualifies-for-womens-100m-semifinals\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Team Nigeria Rosemary Chukwuma has booked her spot in the semifinals of the women's 100m at the Paris 2024 Olympics.  Rosemary secured 3rd position in her first Preliminary Round of the 100m women's race.  She came through in 3rd position in a time of 11.26s, as Dina Asher-Smith of the United States 2nd in 11.01s. While Ewa Swoboda of Poland won the race in a Season's Best of 10.99s.  Rosemary is among the three African women behind Marie Josee-Ta Lou (Ivory Coast) 10.87s and Gina Bass (Gambia) 11.01, who will aim to reach the final.  The women's 100m semi-finals will be held by 6:30 pm on Saturday.  Ancelotti names player he wished he'd coached  NPFL: Sunshine Stars declare three players AWOL  Olympics 2024: I borrowed bicycle from Germans to compete - Nigerian cyclist, Ukpeseraye  Olympics 2024: 'Great rivalry has been created' - Lacazette on France beating Argentina  Olympics 2024: Sports Minister updates on Favour Ofili's 100m race exclusion, raises posers  Olympics 2024 women's football: All 8 countries that qualified for quarter-final [List]  Olympics 2024: Mixed reactions from Nigerians as Super Falcons crash out  Olympics 2024: Stop bad-mouthing Super Falcons - Ayinde rallies support for teammates  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"